Name: Ball Check Valve - 316 Stainless Steel - BSP
Brand: Ball Check Valve - 316 Stainless Steel - BSP
Description:
This 316 stainless steel Ball Check Valve with threaded BSP end connections is manufactured in Italy.

Install in your piping system to prevent back flow.

Keeps your fluid flowing in one direction only.

Very simple operation, using a rubber coated ball, which moves up and down depending on the flow direction. Designed so that the valve will never block up.

The rubber coated ball, provides the seal when the backward flow pushes the ball back on to the valve seat.

Can be installed in many applications such as Marine, Sewage, and any fluid pump system.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only

The Concentric Reducing Rubber Expansion Joint has a centre line which remains the same, and has one end larger or smaller than the other. This enables the pipeline to have some flexibility and connection from one larger pipe to a smaller pipe.

Available in size range DN25 (1") to DN600 (24")

Please advise if one flange is different from the other, for example - large flange is ANSI 150LB and small flange is Table E.

- Higher Pressure Rating available - contact for details

- Different material options available, such as stainless steel flanges, NBR, EPDM or Viton rubber options are available. Contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Control Rod - Rubber Expansion Joint Accessory
Brand: Control Rod - Rubber Expansion Joint Accessory
Description:
Galvanised/ Zinc Plated Control rod for Rubber Expansion Joints.

- Also available in Stainless Steel - contact us for a quote.

When fitted to rubber expansion joints and mating flanges these will stop excessive movement which prevents the rubber expansion joint from failing.

The price is for 1 x control rod. If you need 2 or 4 x control rods, you need to make the quantity 2 or 4 or however many you need.

The price quoted is relevant to the Nominal Bore Size of the rubber expansion joint, and manufactured from Galvansied Steel/ Zinc plated steel.

Please advise what the flange specification is, as the control rods are manufactured to suit the flange specification.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Double Arch Rubber Expansion Joint - unfilled arch
Description:
The Double Arch Rubber Expansion Joint with an unfilled arch provides greater movement and flexibility than a Single Arch. Movements of 40mm and upwards are acheivable with two arches.

Tie rods/Control rods should be installed if excessive movement is likely to occur.

Available in size range DN50 (2") to DN1000

- The double arch can be unfilled or filled depending on the application and customer requirements.

- More allowable movement than a single arch rubber expansion joint.

- Available in a wide range of rubber materials.

- Available in a wide range of flange specifications such as AS4087 PN16, AS2129 Table D, ANSI 150LB/ASME 150.

- Available in a wide range of flange/backing ring materials such as 316 stainless steel, hot dipped galvanised, and zinc plated steel.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Description:
DB-1 Slip On Duckbill Check Valve

The Slip On Duckbill Check Valve model DB-1 is installed over the end of a plain ended pipe to prevent back flow.

The DB-1 model is a Flat bottom model, with a flared top to enhance flow rates and reduce head loss.

Curved Bill features:

The Curved Bill model provides 50% more sealing area compared to the straight bill ended duckbill check valve, enabling a better tighter seal when debris are present. 25mm of fluid/water is all it takes to open the valve.

Measure the Outside Diameter of your pipe to select the size you need. - Product sizing is dependant on the OD of your pipe.

- Available in a wide range of sizes. 88.9mm to 1700.0mm.

- Available in different rubber materials such as Neoprene, NBR, EPDM, Viton etc - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: DB-4 Inline Duckbill Check Valve - EPDM - Clamp type
Brand: Defender Valves Inline Duckbill Check Valve - EPDM
Description:
The DB-4 Inline Duckbill Check Valve using a clamp is to be fitted inside your pipe to prevent back flow. This is an insertable rubber check valve. The end is secured in place by tightening the internal expanding clamp. Additional bolts can be installed in the pre-existing holes in the clamp, drilling will be required. Suited to low back pressure applications.

Size range starting from Pipe ID of 100.0mm to Pipe ID 600.0mm.

The pipe ID (internal diameter) must be advised at the time of requesting a quote or ordering.

Choosing a Curved Bill or Straight Bill:

- Curved Bill model - provides 50% more sealing area compared to the straight bill ended duckbill check valve, enabling a better tighter seal when debris are present. Does require a slightly higher cracking pressure to open the valve compared to the Straight Bill model.

- Straight Bill model - opens with minimal cracking pressure, if debris are present there is a high chance it will effect sealing performance.

 

- Available in a range of rubber materials such as Neoprene, NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: DB-2 Flanged Duckbill Check Valve - AS2129 Table E - Neoprene
Brand: DB-2 Flanged Duckbill Check Valve - AS2129 Table E
Description:
Size range from DN80 to DN1700

The DB-2 Flanged Duckbill Check Valve model can be bolted to the mating flange at the end of a pipe to prevent back flow, or be bolted to a storm water concrete headwall.

Available in a range of different flange specifications such as AS2129 Table E, Table D, ASME 150/ANSI 150LB, AS4087 PN16.

Cracking pressure is 25cm of water/2.48kPa. ( Curved bill )

Head loss is 2kPa average.

2 design options as follows:

- Flared model

- Flat bottom model

Choosing a Curved Bill or Straight Bill:

- Curved Bill model - provides 50% more sealing area compared to the straight bill ended duckbill check valve, enabling a better tighter seal when debris are present. Does require a slightly higher cracking pressure to open the valve compared to the Straight Bill model.

- Straight Bill model - opens with minimal cracking pressure, if debris are present there is a high chance it will effect sealing performance.

Supplied with a 316 stainless steel backing flange, the rubber duckbill check valve will last for many years in operation.

Choose the Neoprene rubber material if the duckbill check valve will be fitted near the Ocean and in contact with salt water.

- Available in a range of different flange specifications on request.

- Available in a range of different rubber materials on request, such as Neoprene, NBR, EPDM, Viton etc.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Duplex Basket Strainer 316SS fitted with 3 way flanged ball valves ANSI 150LB
Brand: Duplex Basket Strainer 316SS fitted with 3 way fla
Description:
The Duplex Basket Strainer is fabricated from 316 Stainless Steel. It comes with 3 way Ball Valves with an L or T port to be specified when ordering.

Description:
The Fabricated Basket Strainer comes fitted with a davit arm for lifting the top lid and a cable hoist to lift out the internal basket screen.

In large sizes of Basket Strainers, internal basket screens become very heavy when full, and it is safer to use a lifting hoist to lift out the internal basket safely.

Name: Foot Valve - Galvanised - Flanged Table D
Brand: Foot Valve - Galvanised - Flanged Table D
Description:
The Galvanised Foot Valve is installed to prevent back flow and losing prime, and prevent large debris from being sucked into the pump system.

Size range: DN80(3") to DN600(24")

Installed under water, or submerged in fluid.

Installed on the suction side of a pump, when the pump turns off, the valve automatically closes by the backwards flow of fluid. This keeps fluid in the suction line, keeping the suction line primed, ready for the next pump start up.

Galvanised Flanged Foot Valves are available in size DN80, DN100, DN125, DN150, DN200, DN250, DN300, DN350, DN400, DN450, DN500, DN550, DN600.

AS2129 Table D flanged.

AS2129 Table E flange on special request. Pricing differs to Table D.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

The HDPE Foot Valve is installed to stop large debris from entering the pump system and stops back flow maintaining priming for the pump. 

Size range: DN80(3") to DN400(16").

Over size DN150(6") The Poly Foot Valve comes with Anti Vortex plates in the screen. No water swirling occurs, maximising an unrestrictive water flow.

Installed on the suction side of a pump. Keep your suction line primed with this valve.

HDPE poly Flanged Foot valves are available in sizes DN80, DN100, DN125, DN150, DN200, DN250, DN300, DN350, DN400.

The Poly Foot Valve can be installed vertically, or at a 45 degrees angle. The disc has a spring closure mechanism.

Available in a range of flange specifications such as Table D, Table E, ANSI 150LB/ ASME 150 - contact us for a quote.

12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Float Valve - Hydraulically Lever Operated - Flanged ANSI 150LB
Brand: Float Valve - Hydraulically Lever Operated - Flang
Description:
Hydraulically Lever Operated Flanged Float valve. Flange specification ANSI 150LB / ASME 150.

Size range DN50(2") to DN150(6").

Application: Clean water only

This Float Valve is hydraulically operated, single seated, piston actuated, internal pilot and float controlled.

At the full supply level, inlet pressure is retained within the piston chamber by the pilot valve, equalising pressures across the piston, and permitting inlet pressure to close the valve.

As the supply level falls, the pilot valve discharges internal pressure allowing inlet pressure within the valve to act upon the larger piston area to lift the valve to a modulating opening.

Water supply authorities and industry throughout Australia accept this robust reliable design and construction which utilises proven materials.

Name: DB-3 Inline Duckbill Check Valve - EPDM - Flanged Table E
Brand: Defender Valves Inline Duckbill Check Valve - EPDM
Description:
The DB-3 Inline Duckbill Check Valve is Flanged Table E and is to be fitted inside your pipe to prevent back flow. This is an insertable rubber check valve. The end is secured in place by the flange. Suited to low back pressure applications.

Size range starting from Pipe ID of 73.0mm.

The pipe ID (internal diameter) must be advised at the time of requesting a quote or ordering.

Choosing a Curved Bill or Straight Bill:

- Curved Bill model - provides 50% more sealing area compared to the straight bill ended duckbill check valve, enabling a better tighter seal when debris are present. Does require a slightly higher cracking pressure to open the valve compared to the Straight Bill model.

- Straight Bill model - opens with minimal cracking pressure, if debris are present there is a high chance it will effect sealing performance.

 

Please advise the flange specification when ordering. Standard is AS2129 Table E.

- Available in a range of flange specifications - contact us for a quote.

- Available in a range of rubber materials such as Neoprene, NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Flex Grip L
Description:
The Flex Grip L model is the Long model pipe coupling. Allowing for axial movements, vibration, and minor pipe misalignments. This coupling does not prevent pull out, so pipes must be anchored somehow.

Measure your pipe outside diameter before selecting the size. Ensure the working pressure is suitable.

- High pressure ratings are available - contact us for a quote

- A range of different rubber materials available such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Flex Grip L 

  • Flexible Design: Accommodates pipe misalignment and axial movement, making it ideal for systems with thermal expansion or dynamic movement.
  • Durable and Reliable: Made from high-quality, corrosion-resistant materials, ensuring longevity in demanding environments.
  • Quick Installation: Requires no welding, flanging, or special tools, reducing labor costs and installation time.

The Orbit Couplings Flex Grip L is a high-performance mechanical coupling designed to connect pipes in various industrial applications. It provides flexibility in pipe alignment and movement while maintaining a secure and leak-proof connection. The coupling is suited for use in systems that experience vibration, pressure changes, and temperature variations, making it perfect for applications such as marine, industrial, and building services.

Features:

  • Flexible pipe connection: Handles axial and angular deflection.
  • Corrosion-resistant materials: Ensures long-term durability.
  • No welding required: Simplifies the installation process.
  • High-pressure and temperature resistance: Suited for industrial and marine use.
  • Vibration absorption: Prevents stress on the piping system.

Note: The Orbit Couplings Flex Grip L is a permanently closed, flexible coupling designed for dynamic piping systems, while the Orbit Couplings Flex Grip Open L allows for easier access due to its openable structure.

Available up to Pipe Outside Diameter size 4000.0mm

Please check your pipe Outside diameter before ordering.

-  Higher Pressure ratings are available - contact us for a quote

Name: Flex Grip 2 S
Description:
The Flex Grip 2 S is the two peice casing model, which can open into two halves for installation. The short model pipe coupling/ repair clamp with two locking mechanisms. Allowing for axial movement. This model is very strong, heavy duty with extra bolts, adding to the working pressure rating.

Low pressure and High pressure versions available. Contact us about your high working pressure applications.

Available up to Pipe Outside Diameter size 4000.0mm

Please check your pipe Outside diameter before ordering.

- High Pressure Pipe Couplings are available - contact us for a quote.

- High Pressure Pipe Repair Clamps are available - contact us for a quote.

- Different rubber material options are available such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Flex Grip Open L
Description:
The Flex Grip Open L model is the opening Long model pipe coupling/ repair clamp for ease of installation and allowing for axial movement. Can also be used as a repair clamp/coupling. Please check your pipe Outside diameter before ordering.

- Higher Pressure ratings available - contact us for a quote.

- Different rubber material options are available such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Flex Grip Open L

  • Openable Design: Allows for quick access to piping systems, making it easier to perform maintenance or repairs without dismantling the entire system.
  • Accommodates Pipe Movement: Flexes to handle axial movement and angular deflection, ideal for dynamic systems.
  • Durable: Built with corrosion-resistant materials, ensuring longevity and reliable performance in various environments.

The Orbit Couplings Flex Grip Open L is a flexible coupling that stands out for its openable design, making it easier to access piping systems for inspection, maintenance, or repairs. It is commonly used in systems with dynamic loads and where regular access is needed. Like the Flex Grip L, it accommodates axial movement and angular deflection, providing a flexible yet secure connection in high-pressure and high-temperature environments.

Features:

  • Openable structure: Provides easy access for maintenance without full disassembly.
  • Flexible connection: Accommodates pipe misalignment and movement.
  • Corrosion-resistant materials: Long-lasting performance in harsh conditions.
  • Quick installation and removal: No welding or flanging required.
  • Vibration absorption: Protects piping systems from stress due to movement or vibrations.

Note: The Orbit Couplings Flex Grip Open L is similar to the Flex Grip L but features an openable design, allowing for easy access for maintenance and inspection without removing the entire coupling.

Name: Flex Grip Stepped
Description:
The Flex Grip Stepped model is the stepped pipe coupling model used to join two pipes with different outside diameters, such as 114.3mm Steel Pipe with 110.0mm Poly Pipe.

This model of pipe coupling does not provide pull out resistance, so pipes will need to be anchored somehow.

Measure the outside diameter of both pipes to be connected to select the correct size coupling.

- Available in a range of sizes - contact us for a quote

- Higher Pressure ratings available - contact us for a quote

- Different rubber material options available such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Flange Adapter Flex Grip S
Description:
The stainless steel flange adapter is a problem solver when no welding can be done on site, and helps the user with a plain ended pipe to connect up to a flange ended pipe connection, using this small section of pipe with a flange on one end, and using a pipe coupling.

- Different sizes, materials, pressure ratings, flange specifications are available - contact us for a quote.

Depending on your requirements different models of pipe couplings can be supplied. Axial movements and flexibility or axial restraint and pull out resistance.

Measure the outside diameter of your plain ended pipe to select the pipe coupling size.

Name: Open Flex 400-L
Description:
The Orbit Couplings Open Flex 400-L model is 400mm long with a two piece casing and a double locking mechanism. 

Size range from 200.0mm to 1016.0mm

Allowing for axial movement, it can be used as a pipe coupling and as a pipe repair clamp.

Being 400mm long, it will allow for a 200mm pipe gap, or 200mm diameter hole in a pipe when a stainless steel strip insert is fitted to the clamp.

Using big rubber sealing lips on each side, this is a heavy duty clamp for sealing pipes with large sections missing.

Casing material options are 316 stainless steel and 304 stainless steel.

Available up to Pipe Outside Diameter size 1016.0mm

Please check your pipe Outside diameter before ordering.

-  Higher Pressure model available - contact us for a quote on the Open Flex 400-LP

- Different rubber material options are available such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only

Name: Plast Coupling
Description:
The Plast Coupling is the easiest pipe coupling model specifically used for connecting plastic pipes such as HDPE pipe. The coupling is designed to provide axial restraint and pull out resistance, using progressive anchor rings. Tightening the two bolts will lock the two pipes together using this mechanical pipe coupling.

This mechanical Plast pipe coupling is used to connect two HDPE pipes together, in a fast and easy manner.

Please ensure your pipe outside diameter matches the size of coupling.

The Plast coupling is sized to suit the Outside diameter of the HDPE pipe. 63mm outside diameter, 75mm outside diameter, 90mm outside diameter, 110mm outside diameter, 125mm outside diameter, 140mm outside diameter, 160mm outside diameter, 180mm outside diameter, 200mm outside diameter, 225mm outside diameter, 250mm outside diameter.

- Different rubber material options are available such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

*Other outside diameter sizes not mentioned can be manufactured on request*

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Orbit Pipe Repair Clamp Series 1 and 200mm long
Description:
The Orbit Pipe Repair Clamp Series 1 and 200mm long with 3 bolts.

Available in pipe OD sizes from 44.0mm to 327.0mm

Series 1 repair clamp benefits

  • Durable and Reliable: Made from high-quality, corrosion-resistant materials, ensuring longevity in demanding environments.
  • Quick Installation: Requires no welding, flanging, or special tools, reducing labor costs and installation time.

The Orbit Pipe Repair Clamp Series 1 is a high-performance mechanical repair clamp designed to seal pipes in various industrial applications. It provides a secure and leak-proof seal. The coupling is suited for use in systems that experience vibration, pressure changes, and temperature variations, making it perfect for applications such as marine, industrial, and building services.

Features:

  • Flexible Casing: The casing is designed to bend and flex so that it can be opened and wrapped around pipe.
  • Corrosion-resistant materials: Ensures long-term durability.
  • No welding required: Simplifies the installation process.
  • Pressure and temperature resistance: Suited for industrial and marine use.
  • Square rubber gasket design: Allows water and fluids to be trapped between the rubber seal design.

 

Wrap around your pipe to seal any leaking hole or crack in your piping system.

Manufactured from 316 stainless steel and rubber.

Very easy to install, with basic tools.

This is for PIPE REPAIR ONLY. This cannot be used as a pipe coupling.

Please check your pipe Outside diameter before ordering.

Price shown is for EPDM rubber or NBR rubber sealing sleeve.

- Different rubber material options are available such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: PTFE Lined Rubber Expansion Joint FSF with Table E or ANSI 150LB Zinc flanges
Brand: PTFE Lined Rubber Expansion Joint FSF with Table E
Description:
The PTFE Lined Rubber Expansion Joint, has an internal PTFE lining fitted to the rubber expansion joint.

Available in size range DN32 to DN600 (24")

PTFE Lined Rubber Expansion Joints should only be installed on a pipeline to eliminate vibration. No large movements can occur with PTFE.

A rubber expansion joint will not expand or compress with a PTFE liner installed. Neither should you expect any angular or lateral movements.

- Different rubber material options are available such as NBR, EPDM, VITON and more - contact us for a quote.

- Different flange material options are available such as 316 stainless steel, Hot dip galvanised, Zinc plated.

- Different flange specification options are available such as AS4087 PN16, DIN 16 etc.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Single Filled Arch Rubber Expansion Joint
Brand: Single Filled Arch Rubber Expansion Joint
Description:
The Single Arch Rubber Expansion Joint with a filled arch, has a smooth straight bore internally, ideal for applications where clogging could occur such as in slurry pipes, or where a greater vacuum pressure is present on a pump suction line. The filled arch model is for vibration elimination on suction pipelines and slurry pipelines.

Allowable movements of 10mm are acheivable with a single filled arch.

Tie Rods/Control rods should be installed when excessive movements are likely to occur.

Available in size range DN25 (1") to DN3500

Slurry bellow

Suction bellow

Also they can be installed on the suction side of pumps as they have a vacuum rating of 750 mm H.g. and dont require a vacuum ring to reach this rating.

Typically Flanged Table E or ANSI 150LB/ASME 150. Available in a range of other flange specifications. Advise us when ordering.

Typically with 50% less expansion, contraction and angular deflection compared with the unfilled single arch model.

- Available in a range of flange materials such as 316 stainless steel - contact us for a quote.

- Available in a range of different rubber materials such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only. If a 24 months warranty is required contact us for a quote.

Name: Straub Fire Fence
Description:
The Straub Fire Fence is a fire resistant coupling to be installed when fire protection is required, such as in an engine room.

Available with two coupling model options being the Straub Metal Grip and the Straub Grip L.

Axially restraining pipe couplings with pull out resistance must be used with the Straub Fire Fence for the joining of pipes.

Straub Metal Grip Fire Fence

Size range: 30.0mm to 457.2mm

Pressure rating: 67 Bar to 8 Bar

 

Straub Grip L Fire Fence

Size range: 26.9mm to 406.4mm

Pressure rating: 46 Bar to 3 Bar

 

Measure the pipe outside diameter to determine the size of the clamp before ordering.

Description:
The Stainless Steel Y Strainer CF8M Flanged ANSI 150LB in 316 stainless steel with a 316 stainless steel filter screen internally. This high quality material provides a long life Y strainer suitable for corrosive environments.

As standard they come with ANSI 150LB Flanges. AS2129 Table E flanges can also be provided please contact us for a quote.

Name: Triple Arch Rubber Expansion Joint
Description:
The Triple Arch Rubber Expansion Joint has three arches which can be filled or unfilled. The triple arch rubber expansion joint provides greater movement and flexibility compared to the single arch and double arch models. Movements of 60mm and upwards are achievable.

Tie Rods/Control rods should be installed if excessive movements are likely to occur.

Available in size range DN50 (2") to DN3000

- Available in a range of sizes and flange options - contact us for a quote.

- Available in a range or rubber material options such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote.

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only. If a 24 months warranty is required contact us for a quote.

Name: Twin Sphere Rubber Expansion Joint FTF with Table E or ANSI 150LB Zinc flanges
Brand: Twin Sphere Rubber Expansion Joint FTF with Table
Description:
The Twin Sphere Rubber Expansion Joint has two spheres providing more flexibility and movement compared to a single sphere model. Also known as a vibration eliminator and rubber bellow.

Allowable movements range from 27mm to 65mm depending on the nominal bore size and direction of movement.

Tie rods/Control rods should be installed when excessive movements are likely to occur.

Available in size range DN25 (1") to DN750 (30")

Most common flanges are Table E or ANSI 150LB, advise when ordering, and that the same flange specification is the same on both ends. It can be common for different flanges to fitted on each end.

- Available in a range of different flange specifications - contact us for a quote.

- Available in a range of flange materials such as 316 stainless steel - contact us for a quote.

- Available in a range of different rubber materials such as NBR, EPDM, Viton - contact us for a quote

- 12 months warranty on manufacturing defects only.

Name: Heavy Duty Y Strainer Filter Screen - SS316
Subtitle: Heavy Duty Y Strainer Filter Screen - SS316
Brand: Heavy Duty Y Strainer Filter Screen
Description:
The Heavy Duty Y Strainer filter screen is manufactured from 316 stainless steel, with added strengthening and cross bars.

With the added cross bars, removing a dirty screen is made much easier, as well as easier installation of the filter screen once cleaned.

Note: Y strainer filter screens without cross bars can be very difficult to remove from the Y strainer at service time, and generally dont last as long.

Heavy Duty Y strainer filter screens are designed for very demanding processes in pipelines, such as high pressure, and large heavy debris that would ruin a normal cheaper filter screen.

Essential dimensions required are as follows: Screen Outside Diameter, Inside diameter, Length, mesh size. Must be advised when ordering.

 

- Also available in different materials - contact us for a quote.
